00:16:57.020 --> 00:17:02.059
So we really spent a lot of time working on our data governance, our policies, and our

00:17:02.059 --> 00:17:08.140
protections, and we spent a lot of time building that out in the person event data environment.

00:17:08.140 --> 00:17:09.380
It's a secure environment.

00:17:09.380 --> 00:17:10.380
You can't download anything.

00:17:10.380 --> 00:17:13.020
You can't take anything out of the environment.

00:17:13.060 --> 00:17:16.260
People get fussy about that because it makes it hard to access, and you've got to request

00:17:16.260 --> 00:17:20.380
access through a project to certain things.

00:17:20.380 --> 00:17:27.180
But that, at least, when people are realizing that nobody's going to pull everything into

00:17:27.180 --> 00:17:30.979
a CSV file or a spreadsheet that's going to be sitting on their desktop, that provides

00:17:30.979 --> 00:17:32.579
